crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a malicious dropper that establishes persistence via a LaunchAgent. It creates a directory `~/Library/LaunchAgents` and drops a plist file (`com.<username>.glhyrjkdmqcabbwj.plist`) to ensure it runs on login. It also writes an AppleScript payload to `~/Library/glhyrjkdmqcabbwj`. This script is designed to fetch a Command and Control (C2) server address by scraping a Telegram channel page (`https://t[.]me/phefuckxiabot`) and then communicates with the C2 for further instructions. The binary also daemonizes itself and kills the Terminal application.
